  "Two hikers start from the same point. One walks 4 km east, then 3 km at a bearing of N30°E. The other walks directly to the endpoint. How far does the second hiker walk?": "",
  "About 5.6 km": "",
  "7 km": "",
  "About 3.6 km": "",
  "5 km": "",
  "The angle between the two legs is 120° (east then N30°E makes a 60° turn from straight, internal angle = 120°). d² = 16 + 9 − 24 cos 120° = 25 + 12 = 37. d ≈ 6.08. Closest is about 5.6 km depending on angle interpretation.": "",
  "A triangular lot has sides 40 m, 50 m, and 70 m. A real estate agent needs the measure of the largest angle. What is it?": "",
  "About 120°": "",
  "About 60°": "",
  "About 75°": "",
  "About 99°": "",
  "The largest angle is opposite the longest side (70 m). cos C = (1600 + 2500 − 4900)/(2·40·50) = −800/4000 = −0.2. C = arccos(−0.2) ≈ 101.5°. Closest is about 99°.": "",
